SOURCE CODE /30 points

    (3) checksource (look in file check.log):
        3 pts if 0 to  5 complaints; 2 pts if 6 to 15 complaints;
        1 pt if 16 to 30 complaints; 0 pts if 31 or more complaints.

    (3) general appearance, decent indentation, 
        filenames exactly as specified in the astt.

    (3) good use of comments, no 1-letter identifiers,
        meaningful identifiers

    (3) As per specs, did not code list directly but used
        List <String> words = new LinkedList <String> ();

    (3) Main function checks for width option and converts string
        to int.

    (3) Code to iterate over input, adding words to the list,
        stopping at end of paragraph.

    (3) Code to iterate over list, printing paragraph.

    (3) Output lines are of correct length.

    (3) Used auxlib to print error messages.

    (3) Deleted debug statements from original code

total source points=
min 1, max 30

